narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you're thinking of taking French 140 you either have to, for the language requirement, or you know how these lower-level language classes work (everyday classes, everyday homework, history, culture, and readings). So I won't bore you with why I hated the course. If you for whatever reason are considering a language course, I recommend that you take French 140 with professor Bedoui. She clearly knows what she's doing in terms of French language, culture (she's lived in Tunisia and France), and teaching. I frequently left class feeling happy about how it went, despite not being interested in the material, not having done the homework, and having to run to and from class at 9:25 in the morning.
YESSSS honestly and amazing class that wasn't that hard
A lot of work. Take it seriously and your French will get a lot better (mostly in terms of grammar and written work).

A lot of work - class time, homework, assignments, and quizzes are a lot. Learned a lot of French though and am confident about going to France. Depends on professor - Very nice and supportive. Helpful and encouraging. Sometimes rambles and doesn't get to all the work though.
